VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT \b(printf|fprintf|sprintf|vsprintf)\s*\(\s*[^"]+\s*,
WHEN EXPR MISSING:"%s"|"%d"|"%f"|"%i"|"%u"|"%x" && MISSING:const\s+char\s*\*\s*format
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects usage of format functions with potentially unsafe input.
TRACE Externalized rule logic for Potential Format String Attack.
